<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Racial Annimosity</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Hawthorne">Hawthorne</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:40 a.m. 25/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Racial Annimosity<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1710" TARGET=_self>HELLO</A> (Rainman)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>&gt; On another note, what is up with CC splitting up into Drow and
<BR>&gt; Good race? I'm a firm believer that your guild should be only
<BR>&gt; Drow or only Good. Anyone else agree? Whats going to happen when
<BR>&gt; DEs attack Halflings or what happends with Druids attacking DEs?
<P>Hiya Rain, lemme take a stab at this.
<BR>Most people have a character prefrence such as halfing, elf etc. I understand your point about class warfare, and good race's and bad race's and how they dont mix in the RPG Environment that 989 has in place. However, a large majority of the Core PvP community overlook that and have choosen thier race based off of class statistics and , and not how that race may stand socially in the RPG aspect of the game. Its purley a powergamer move. The PvP server IMHO will house 2 distinct factions, the pure racial factions, and then the Guild factions. Ofcourse guild factions will ignore the racial balance of the game for the most part inorder to serve the guild and play as a unit (again, a powergamer move).
<P>I would suggest that people on this server get familliar with the guilds that are represneted there. This may make it easy on some players to understand why there isnt going to be "racial harmony" amoung your own race.
<P>&gt; And people, remember that you are playing on a PvP Server. I'm
<BR>&gt; getting sick of people yelling WHY DID YOU ATTACK ME or WHY DID
<BR>&gt; YOU LOOT ME. Another thing I don't get is when I challenge ppl
<BR>&gt; to duels of a higher or equal level to me and they just run off.
<P>Agreed totaly. The thing about the PvP server is that it is just that, PvP, home of the K-RaD dudes, kewlz00r pk's, good evil role players, hard-core antis, the solo killer, the asshole, powergammers, Lynch mobs, and the typical RPG player.
<P>My advice to people is that if you arent willing to deal with the diversities of the PvP server such as inner racial annimosity or looting and dueling constantly, then I suggest another server.
<P>Hawthorne EQ-Adept, Council - The Regulators
<BR>www.theregulators.org
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
